  <para>
    This command changes which object the &layers; in a &layerset;
    will display.  In the GUI, the command is invoked by changing the
    <guilabel>category</guilabel> and <guilabel>object</guilabel>
    menus in the <guilabel>Displayed Object</guilabel> pane of the
    &layereditor;.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <varname>category</varname> argument is the name of a class of
    displayable &oof2; objects: one of &micro;, &image;, &skel;,
    &mesh;, <link
    linkend="Section-Concepts-Microstructure-ActiveArea"><classname>Active
    Area</classname></link>, or <link
    linkend="Section-Concepts-Microstructure-PixelSelection"><classname>Pixel
    Selection</classname></link>.  In the GUI, changing the category
    invalidates all of the <link
    linkend="RegisteredClass-DisplayMethod"><classname>DisplayMethods</classname></link>
    listed in the right hand pane of the &layereditor; window.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <varname>object</varname> argument is the <link
      linkend="Section-Concepts-Path">path</link> to an existing
    object in the selected <varname>category</varname>.
  </para>

